In [[1485]] (17th year of the [[Bunmei era]]), the temple received a land grant from {{ill|Yamana Masatoyo|ja|山名政豊|12=draft}}, demonstrating its historical significance.<ref>Yamana Masatoyo’s Myoken Shrine Land Grant (document held by Nikko-in) {{harv|Hyogo Prefectural Archaeological Museum|2010|p=38}}.</ref>
