In {{ill|1485|en|1485|WD=Q6644|lt=1485|1=1485}} (17th year of the [[Bunmei era]]), the temple received a land grant from {{ill|Yamana Masatoyo|ja|山名政豊|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamana Masatoyo|1=Masatoyo Yamana|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11467585}}, demonstrating its historical significance.<ref>Yamana Masatoyo’s Myoken Shrine Land Grant (document held by Nikko-in) {{harv|Hyōgo Prefectural Archaeological Museum|2010|p=38}}.</ref>
